free_txt: Diatomic deuterium ions accelerated to 220 keV
Correction for inscattering of 13% of measured total
Stilbene scintillator used as neutron detector
Diatomic deuterium ions accelerated to 220 keV
Neutrons produced in a thick Zr-T target. Neutron
beam at an angle of 88 deg with respect to deuterium
Transmission method in good geometry was used.
Neutron detector was placed at a distance of 165 cm
from neutron source. The samples were placed halfway
between the source and detector. The thickness of
samples was chosen to give transmission of 50%. Most
of the samples had a diameter of 2.54 cm.
Associated alpha particle from D-T reaction
and additional scintillation detector were used
Data taken from tab. 1 of the PR,88,562,1952
